{"lemma":"راهِبٌ","slug":"راهِبٌ","root":"ر.ه.ب","root_slug":"ر-ه-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-ه-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n16839"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D8%A7%D9%87%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"monk","examples":[{"text":"ذَٰلِكَ بِأَنَّ مِنْهُمْ قِسِّيسِينَ وَرُهْبَانًا وَأَنَّهُمْ لَا يَسْتَكْبِرُونَ","english":"For there are among them priests and monks and they are not haughty."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"priest","tags":["dialectal"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Perhaps derived from the active participle of رَهِبَ (rahiba, “to dread”), from the root ر ه ب (r h b), with the intermediate meanings \"dreader\", \"God-fearer\", \"God-worshiper\", \"venerator\"; compare رَهَب (rahab, “veneration, respect”) and رَهْبَة (rahba, “terror; dread; awe”)."},"ipa":["/raː.hib/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n16839","headword_ar":"رَاهِبٌ","root":"rhb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fearing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fearer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fearing with caution;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a cautious fearer;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa raAhibN mina A@ll~`hi","text_ar":"هُوَ رَاهِبٌ مِنَ ا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who fears God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fearer of God;"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: whence the signification"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1169},{"kind":"text","text":"next following. (Msb.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A Christian"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"monk, ascetic, religious recluse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"devotee;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who devotes himself to religious services"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exercises, in a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SawomaEap","text_ar":"صَوْمَعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cell"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhobaAn","text_ar":"رُهْبَان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the Christians:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) [i. e.] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhobaAnN","text_ar":"رُهْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Mgh, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahabapN","text_ar":"رَهَبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (A;) or, sometimes,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhobaAnN","text_ar":"رُهْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a sing.; (K;) as in the following ex., cited by IAar:"},{"kind":"quote","text":"lawo kal~amato ruhobaAna dayorK fiY Alqulalo\n                      \n                     \n                        laA@noHadara Alr~uhobaAnu yasoEaY fanazalo"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"If she spoke to a Christian monk in a monastery among the summits of a mountain, the Christian monk would come down running, and so descend"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: but he says that the approved way is to use it as a pl.: (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahaAbiynu","text_ar":"رَهَابِينُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. (A, Msb, K) of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhobaAnN","text_ar":"رُهْبَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rahaAbinapN","text_ar":"رَهَابِنَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is another pl. (A, K) of the same, and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruhobaAnuwna","text_ar":"رُهْبَانُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marohuwbN","text_ar":"مَرْهُوبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","Mgh","Msb","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}